<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
        
        <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.2.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-GJzZqFGwb1QTTN6wy59ffF1BuGJpLSa9DkKMp0DgiMDm4iYMj70gZWKYbI706tWS" crossorigin="anonymous">
        <title>TinyApp</title>
    </head>

    <body style="font-size:20px; padding:50px;">

        <% include partials/_header %>

        <h3>User Registration</h3>

        <form class="form-inline" action="/register" method="POST">
        <div class="form-group mb-2">
            <label for="longURL">Email Address:</label>
            <input class="form-control" type="text" name="email" placeholder="Email" style="width: 300px; margin: 1em" required minlength="3">
            <label for="longURL">Password:</label>
            <input class="form-control" type="password" name="password" placeholder="Password" style="width: 300px; margin: 1em" required minlength="3">
            <button type="submit" name="logout-button" class="btn btn-primary">Register</button>
        </div>
        </form>

    </body>
</html>





<!
Create a new template that includes a form with an email address and password field. 
The email field should use type=email and have name=email. 
The password field should use type=password and have name=password. The form should POST to /register.
In express_server.js Create a GET /register endpoint, which returns the template you just created.
